<subSubSection id="C32F65354E07FFC3978807F8FCA145AF" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E07FFC1978807F8FBF74350" blockId="32.[151,1436,1446,2011]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E07FFC1978807F8FE9940C4" bold="true" box="[151,266,1446,1471]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Maxillary palpomere 
<date id="FF8B107E4E07FFC1950E07F9FDD140C4" box="[529,578,1447,1471]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
IV 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1952707F9FDD140C4" box="[568,578,1447,1471]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1955107F9FDCF40C4" box="[590,604,1447,1471]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than labial palpomere III. Pronotum with lateral margins slightly divergent posteriad, posterior angle strongly projected, acute and fairly straight down. Abdominal sternum VI with lantern as long and wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC196FB07B1FE7D437C" box="[484,494,1519,1543]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC196E707B1FD9B437C" box="[504,520,1519,1543]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
sternum length and width, abdominal sternum VII with lantern as long as 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1926707B1FA17437C" box="[1400,1412,1519,1543]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1929107B1FA0F437C" box="[1422,1436,1519,1543]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="4.0">4</number>
sternum length and as wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC196F1044DFE6B4350" box="[494,504,1555,1579]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1951C044DFD804350" box="[515,531,1555,1579]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
sternum width. Pygidium with median lobe beveled.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E07FFC197D80468FB3643EC" blockId="32.[151,1436,1446,2011]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E07FFC197D80468FECB4334" bold="true" box="[199,344,1590,1615]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Colouration</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E07FFC196690468FE5D4334" box="[374,462,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,202,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[155,1431,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Habitus. 10 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 11 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 12 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 13 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 14 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 15 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 16 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 17 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 18 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252105/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC196AC0469FE5D4334" box="[435,462,1591,1615]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) Integument dark-brown. Fronto-clypeus, antenna base, pronotum disc, pro and mesocoxas and mesosternum yellowish-brown. Antennomeres with flabellum gradually darkening toward apex, from yellowish-brown to dark-brown. Prothorax with expansions pale yellow. Elytron black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E07FFC197D804FCFCF44230" blockId="32.[151,1436,1446,2011]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E07FFC197D804FCFE9443C0" bold="true" box="[199,263,1698,1723]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Head</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E07FFC1960204FCFEEF43C0" box="[285,380,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 40" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1758,1781]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,204,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1737]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 40. Frons shape drawings 23 Amydetes agnita. 24 A. apicalis. 25 A. discissa. 26 A. fastigiata. 27 A. fucata. 28 A. lucioloides. 29 Amydetes solaris sp. nov.. 30 Amydetes goiana sp. nov.. 31 Amydetes manezinha sp. nov.. 32 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 33 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 34 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 35 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 36 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 37 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 38 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 39 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 40 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 250 µm. DBA = distance between antennifers antennifers. DBAS = distance between antennal sockets." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252107/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
Figs. 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1964204FDFEEF43C0" box="[349,380,1699,1723]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="32.51">32</number>
</figureCitation>
, 51) Fronto-clypeus slightly depressed up to antennal sockets, anterior margin 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC193E704FDFA9043C0" box="[1272,1283,1699,1723]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1921104FDFA8F43C0" box="[1294,1308,1699,1723]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="3.0">3</number>
wider than distance between antennal sockets and slightly wider than distance between antennifers. Antenna with 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1929F0499FA0F43A4" box="[1408,1436,1735,1759]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="40.0">40</number>
antennomeres (n= 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1967804B5FEE54278" box="[359,374,1771,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
); antennomere 
<date id="FF8B107E4E07FFC1953404B5FDCE4278" box="[555,605,1770,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
III 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1954C04B4FDCE4278" box="[595,605,1770,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1957704B4FDE44278" box="[616,631,1770,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="5.0">5</number>
longer than pedicel, with flabellum 
<date id="FF8B107E4E07FFC1933804B5FBD04278" box="[1063,1091,1771,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1933804B5FBA64278" box="[1063,1077,1771,1795]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than antennomere III. Labrum with anterior margin straight. Maxillary palpomere IV 
<date id="FF8B107E4E07FFC194420551FCEB425C" box="[861,888,1807,1831]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC194420551FCF8425C" box="[861,875,1807,1831]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer than III, 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1932F0551FBA8425C" box="[1072,1083,1807,1831]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC1935A0551FBC0425C" box="[1093,1107,1807,1831]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than labial palpomere III. Gular sutures as separeted as maxillary palpomere IV width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E07FFC197D80508FC9A42A0" blockId="32.[151,1436,1446,2011]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E07FFC197D80508FEB34214" bold="true" box="[199,288,1878,1903]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">Thorax</emphasis>
. (Figs. 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC196630509FE554214" box="[380,454,1879,1903]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="70.88">70, 88</number>
) Pronotum with lateral margins slightly divergent posteriad, posterior angle strongly projected, acute and fairly straight down; setigerous punctures irregularly separeted 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC193990525FB3C42E8" box="[1158,1199,1915,1939]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">
1– 
<date id="FF8B107E4E07FFC193BF0525FB3C42E8" box="[1184,1199,1915,1939]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">2</date>
</number>
x the diameter of a puncture. Hypomeron 
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E07FFC1968B05C1FE2542CD" box="[404,438,1951,1974]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="233">ca.</emphasis>
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC196A205C1FE5B42CC" box="[445,456,1951,1975]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E07FFC196CC05C1FE7242CC" box="[467,481,1951,1975]" pageId="32" pageNumber="233" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than high. Elytron slightly dehiscent; marginal costa with anterior margin not projected. Mesosternum with posterior margin rounded.
</paragraph>
