<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E06FFC097D80410FBAB4289" blockId="33.[151,1437,1614,2035]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E06FFC097D80410FEAF431C" bold="true" box="[199,316,1614,1639]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Abdomen</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E06FFC096470410FE5B431C" box="[344,456,1614,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 116 – 124" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[237,1354,182,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[231,1355,181,1545]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 116 – 124. Abdomen, ventral. Note the lanterns and posterior margin of abdominal sternite V and VIII. 116 Amydetes caetite sp. nov .. 117 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov .. 118 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 119 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 120 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 121 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov .. 122 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 123 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov. 124 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252114/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Figs. 116</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E06FFC096C40411FD94431C" box="[475,519,1615,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 134 – 142" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1548,1571]" captionTargetBox="[257,1322,209,1521]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[247,1339,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 134 – 142. Pygidium, dorsal. 134 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 135 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 136 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov. 6. 137 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 138 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 139 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 140 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 141 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 11. 142 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 500 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252116/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">134</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E06FFC095060411FDEF431C" box="[537,636,1615,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 184 – 195" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[260,1331,198,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[248,1339,193,1440]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 184 – 195. Terminalia. FIGURES 184, 188 and 192 syntergite (dorsal) abdominal sternite IX (ventral). FIGURES 185 – 187, 189 – 191, 193 – 195 Aedeagus, dorsal (185, 189, 193), ventral (186, 190 e 194), lateral (187, 191, 195). FIGURES 184 – 187 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 188 – 191 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 192 – 195 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. Scale. 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252121/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
184– 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC0954D0411FDEF431C" box="[594,636,1615,1639]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="187.0">187</number>
</figureCitation>
) Abdominal sternum V with posterior margin straight or irregular. Abdominal sternum VIII with posterior margin irregular or with posterior margin discreetly projected. Abdominal sternum VI with lantern as long and wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC0959204C9FD0443D4" box="[653,663,1687,1711]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC095BE04C9FD2243D4" box="[673,689,1687,1711]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="2.0">2</number>
sternum length and width. Abdominal sternum VII with lantern as long as 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC097F204E5FF6A43A8" box="[237,249,1723,1747]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC0961D04E5FE8343A8" box="[258,272,1723,1747]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="4.0">4</number>
sternum length and as wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC0957504E5FDE743A8" box="[618,628,1723,1747]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC0956004E5FD1C43A8" box="[639,655,1723,1747]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="2.0">2</number>
sternum width. Pygidium with median lobe discreetly beveled, as ong as or slightly short than lateral lobe, and as wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC095CD0481FD4F438C" box="[722,732,1759,1783]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC095F90481FD66438C" box="[742,757,1759,1783]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior margin width; indentation between lateral lobe and median lobe developed; lateral lobe developed and acuminate. 
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E06FFC0947F055CFC7E4260" bold="true" box="[864,1005,1794,1819]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Terminalia:</emphasis>
Syntergite with anterior and posterior margin symmetrics, anterior margin rounded and rudimentary; suture between abdominal tergites IX and X conspicuous. Abdominal sternum IX oblongo, 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC095B60515FD274218" box="[681,692,1867,1891]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC095A00515FD5E4218" box="[703,717,1867,1891]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than wide; 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC094BC0515FC3D4218" box="[931,942,1867,1891]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC094A70515FC554218" box="[952,966,1867,1891]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than syntergite; wider at posterior 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC097880531FF3142FC" box="[151,162,1903,1927]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC097B10531FF2E42FC" box="[174,189,1903,1927]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="3.0">3</number>
; with lateral margins divergent posteriad up to 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC095CB0531FD7342FC" box="[724,736,1903,1927]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC095F60531FD6442FC" box="[745,759,1903,1927]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="4.0">4</number>
sternum length, bristled and slightly pigmented at posterior 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC0978805CDFF3142D0" box="[151,162,1939,1963]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC097B305CDFF2E42D0" box="[172,189,1939,1963]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="2.0">2</number>
; anterior margin sinuous. 
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E06FFC0951805CCFD1742D0" bold="true" box="[519,644,1938,1963]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Phallobase discreetly asymmetric. Parameres basally constricted, divergent posteriad. Paramere and phallum apically rounded. Phallum 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC094C505E9FC7742B4" box="[986,996,1975,1999]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E06FFC094F105E9FC6D42B4" box="[1006,1022,1975,1999]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" value="4.0">4</number>
longer than paramere, with lateral margins sinuous, ventral plate weakly sclerotized, discreetly enlarged toward apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E05FFC397D802C9FCA145AF" blockId="34.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC397D802C9FEE445CB" bold="true" box="[199,375,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Type-material.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="548E881C4E05FFC3966002C9FE7F45CB" box="[383,492,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Holotype</typeStatus>
: 
<collectingCountry id="F322762E4E05FFC396E802C6FDF345CB" box="[503,608,152,176]" name="Brazil" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">BRAZIL</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3957302C7FD6A45CB" box="[620,761,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Mato grosso</emphasis>
: Barra do Tapirapé, 
<date id="FF8B107E4E05FFC394FB02C9FBA945CB" box="[996,1082,151,176]" bridgedPair="/" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1963-02">
II/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC3931E02C9FBA945CB" box="[1025,1082,151,176]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</date>
, B. Malkin col., male (
<collectionCode id="ED24AE7B4E05FFC3925F02C6FA1C45CB" box="[1344,1423,152,176]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">MZSP</collectionCode>
); one male 
<typeStatus id="548E881C4E05FFC3961B02E3FEF845AE" box="[260,363,189,213]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Paratype</typeStatus>
: 
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3966B02E2FE3945AF" box="[372,426,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">idem</emphasis>
<date id="FF8B107E4E05FFC396AD02E2FD8845AE" box="[434,539,188,213]" bridgedPair="/" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1960-12">
XII/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC396FC02E2FD8845AE" box="[483,539,188,213]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</date>
, B. Malkin col. (
<collectionCode id="ED24AE7B4E05FFC395C802E2FCB545AF" box="[727,806,188,212]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">MZSP</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32F65354E05FFC397D80281FEAA4466" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E05FFC397D80281FEAA4466" blockId="34.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC397D80281FEDD4583" bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC3964A02BEFE35458C" box="[341,422,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caetite" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3964A02BEFE35458C" box="[341,422,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Caetite</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means Cerrado in tupi-guarani language (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B4F4E05FFC3946002BEFB874583" author="Bueno" box="[895,1044,224,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" refString="Bueno, S. (1987) Vocabulario tupi-guarani - portugues. 5 ª. ed. Brasileiros Editora, Sao Paulo, 629 pp." type="book" year="1987">
Bueno, 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC394C702BEFB874583" box="[984,1044,224,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Cerrado is the biome in which 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC3929B02BEFF714467" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caetite">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3929B02BEFF714467" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">A. caetite</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dwells.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32F65354E05FFC397D80379FAFD448F" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8A36BE4E05FFC397D80379FAFD448F" blockId="34.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC397D80379FEA8443B" bold="true" box="[199,315,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC3965D0376FE6C4444" box="[322,511,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caetite">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3965D0376FE6C4444" box="[322,511,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Amydetes caetite</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC395620376FC9A443B" box="[637,777,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucernula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC395620376FC9A443B" box="[637,777,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">A. lucernula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC394100379FCFA443B" bold="true" box="[783,873,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27257D74E05FFC394100379FCFA443B" box="[783,873,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E05FFC394670376FC54443B" box="[888,967,296,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,202,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[155,1431,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Habitus. 10 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 11 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 12 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 13 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 14 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 15 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 16 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 17 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 18 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252105/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
FIG. 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC394B10376FC54443B" box="[942,967,296,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC3931A0376FBEA4444" box="[1029,1145,296,319]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vivianii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3931A0376FBEA4444" box="[1029,1145,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">A. vivianii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3939F0379FB49443B" bold="true" box="[1152,1242,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27257D74E05FFC3939F0379FB49443B" box="[1152,1242,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130E2A3B4E05FFC393F60379FAA8443B" box="[1257,1339,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,202,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[155,1431,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Habitus. 10 Amydetes caetite sp. nov.. 11 Amydetes lucernula sp. nov.. 12 Amydetes plaumanni sp. nov.. 13 Amydetes bellorum sp. nov.. 14 Amydetes itatiaia sp. nov.. 15 Amydetes vivianii sp. nov.. 16 Amydetes marajoara sp. nov.. 17 Amydetes vagalume sp. nov.. 18 Amydetes luzecu sp. nov. Scale. 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252105/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
FIG. 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC3923F0379FAA8443B" box="[1312,1339,295,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), from it differs by abdominal sternum 
<date id="FF8B107E4E05FFC396F90313FD86441F" box="[486,533,332,356]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
IX 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC395150312FD86441F" box="[522,533,332,356]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC395000312FDBE441F" box="[543,557,332,356]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="3.0">3</number>
longer than syntergite (
<date id="FF8B107E4E05FFC394290312FCC0441F" box="[822,851,332,356]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC394290312FCD7441F" box="[822,836,332,356]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
longer in the quoted species). 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC393B90312FA83441F" box="[1190,1296,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caetite">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC393B90312FA83441F" box="[1190,1296,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">A. caetite</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC39788032EFEB644F3" box="[151,293,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucernula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC39788032EFEB644F3" box="[151,293,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">A. lucernula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC396310331FE1944F3" bold="true" box="[302,394,367,392]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27257D74E05FFC396310331FE1944F3" box="[302,394,367,392]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by abdominal sternum VI with lanterns as long and wide as 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC3934D032EFBCF44F3" box="[1106,1116,368,392]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC39379032EFBE644F3" box="[1126,1141,368,392]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="2.0">2</number>
stenum length and width (lantern almost as long as 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC396CB03CAFE4D44D7" box="[468,478,404,428]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC396F703CAFE6B44D7" box="[488,504,404,428]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="2.0">2</number>
sternum length and less than 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC3947D03CAFCFE44D7" box="[866,877,404,428]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC3946803CAFC1644D7" box="[887,901,404,428]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="3.0">3</number>
sternum width in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC3937A03CAFB6644D7" box="[1125,1269,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucernula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3937A03CAFB6644D7" box="[1125,1269,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">A. lucernula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3921F03CAFACD44D6" bold="true" box="[1280,1374,404,429]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27257D74E05FFC3921F03CAFACD44D6" box="[1280,1374,404,429]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) and pronotum with posterior angle strongly projected. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D3D4E05FFC3946F03E6FBA544B4" box="[880,1078,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vivianii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3946F03E6FBA544B4" box="[880,1078,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Amydetes vivianii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B941EAAC4E05FFC3932203E9FB0444AB" bold="true" box="[1085,1175,439,464]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27257D74E05FFC3932203E9FB0444AB" box="[1085,1175,439,464]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the smaller lanterns (abdominal sternum VI and VII with lanterns as long as and with slightly more than 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC393560382FBC6448F" box="[1097,1109,476,500]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFD24994E05FFC393400382FBFE448F" box="[1119,1133,476,500]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" value="4.0">4</number>
width of these sterna).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
